<!-- ══════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="slide" id="s7" data-idx="6" style="background:#fffdf8;">
  <div style="max-width:820px;width:100%;">
    <div class="label">The Exercise</div>
    <h2>CEO + Marching.<br><span class="accent-text">Four Steps.</span></h2>
    <p class="lead">Read all four steps before you start. Then go to the next slide, hit the timer, and do the rep.</p>

    <div class="exercise-track" id="exerciseTrack">
      <div class="ex-step">
        <div class="ex-node">1</div>
        <div class="ex-phase">Choose your prompt</div>
        <h4>Pick something you can answer in 30–60 seconds.</h4>
        <p>Simple enough that the pressure comes from the marching — not from a complicated topic. Choose one below, or use your own.</p>
        <div class="ex-prompts" id="promptPills">
          <div class="ex-prompt-pill" onclick="pickPrompt(this)">"What is one thing I am learning in this challenge?"</div>
          <div class="ex-prompt-pill" onclick="pickPrompt(this)">"What is one communication pattern I want to change?"</div>
          <div class="ex-prompt-pill" onclick="pickPrompt(this)">"What is one idea I believe strongly right now?"</div>
          <div class="ex-prompt-pill" onclick="pickPrompt(this)">"Why does this work matter to me?"</div>
          <div class="ex-prompt-pill" onclick="pickPrompt(this)">"What did I learn from Day 5?"</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="ex-step">
        <div class="ex-node">2</div>
        <div class="ex-phase">Build your CEO answer before you start</div>
        <h4>Structure the answer. Then march. Not the other way around.</h4>
        <p><strong>Core message:</strong> What is my main point?<br>
        <strong>Explain:</strong> What is one clear reason or example?<br>
        <strong>Own the ending:</strong> How will I land it — precisely?</p>
        <p style="margin-top:10px;">The marching does not replace the structure. It pressure-tests it.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ex-step">
        <div class="ex-node">3</div>
        <div class="ex-phase">March and speak — simultaneously</div>
        <h4>Start marching at a steady rhythm. Then speak.</h4>
        <div class="ex-rules">
          <div class="ex-rule">Keep the rhythm constant — do not slow your feet when speaking gets hard</div>
          <div class="ex-rule">Stay with one clear answer — no tangents</div>
          <div class="ex-rule">Aim for 30–60 seconds of continuous speaking</div>
          <div class="ex-rule">Finish the ending cleanly before you stop marching</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="ex-step">
        <div class="ex-node">4</div>
        <div class="ex-phase">Reflect immediately after</div>
        <h4>Answer these four questions right after the rep ends.</h4>
        <div class="ex-rules">
          <div class="ex-rule">What broke first — breath, rhythm, structure, or clarity?</div>
          <div class="ex-rule">Did I hold the CEO structure under load?</div>
          <div class="ex-rule">Did I own the ending or did it disappear?</div>
          <div class="ex-rule">Where exactly did my feet slow down?</div>
        </div>
      </div>
